race.comment: DIETRICH (8) is yet to miss the top three in five starts. Easily won her maiden over 1000m here first-up then showed a nice change of gears but found a couple a little better last start, again over the Gosford 1000m. Cherry ripe now and should appreciate the slightly longer journey. WISNIERSKA (7) returns from an 18-week spell. Filled a minor placing when fresh from a spell last prep in an open two-year-old race at Randwick. Progressive filly who should be ready to run well following two recent trials. BONDASONG (3) was scratched from Race 6 to be kept for this. Disappointed at Kembla last time but has only raced twice so deserves the benefit of the doubt. SENSHI (11) hasn't won for a long while but can improve today dropping back in distance. BOSS (4) has been freshened up since an impressive win in a BM82 at Muswellbrook a month ago. Drops 4kgs and should be competitive.
